          <h2 class="op1">About Yellr</h2>
          <p class="about-p">
            WXXI Public Radio has partnered with HackHackers Rochester to develop Yellr, a new Citizen Journalism mobile app designed to widen audience engagement, especially among younger, technologically-driven and under-represented community members.
            <br/><br/>
            <a href="/local" class="button">Join The Conversation</a>
          </p>
          <p class="about-p">
            The platform – in English and Spanish - enables broad participation from community members in sharing and posting news and other community related information and events.  The project was seeded by a grant funded by the John S. and James L. Knight Foundation, administered by the Institute for Nonprofit News.
          </p>
          <br/></br>
