          <section id="engagement">
            <h3 class="op2">Citizen Engagement</h3>
            <div class="flex-netbook">
              <div class="flex-2">
              <p>
              A group of educational and media partners are working together to promote the technology and encourage participation and exchange. Student groups at RIT are working to rollout uptake of the app amongst a number of Rochester committees including LGBT students and church-based youth groups in the city’s 19th Ward. The goal is to empower those traditionally under-represented communities with a platform that can enable them to share their perspectives and respond to a variety of community news assignments. Ultimately that content will also be used to enhance and expand the range of voices distributed through public media outlets, like WXXI News.
              </p>
              </div>
              <figure class="flex-3"><img src="static/one-pager/img/IMG_2589_small.JPG"></figure>
            </div>
          </section>
          <section id="aggregation" class="flex-netbook alt-layout">
            <div class="flex-2">
              <h3 class="op2">News Aggregation</h3>
              <p>
              WXXI is committed to finding new ways to reach wider audiences including the younger, technologically-driven generation as well as the under-represented population of the local community in upstate New York. The app offers new and enhanced ways for these communities to engage in local and, possibly in the future, national society. It is designed to be an “open source platform” that can be shared with other public television and radio stations in upstate New York and other regions in the future.
              </p>
            </div>
